  - step: Install each package of Virtuozzo (PTA for Windows and Linux).
    check: Make sure installer for each package contains EULA.
  - step: Read the text of EULA.
    check: "Make sure it conforms to the text on http://www.odin.com/legal/"
  - step: Search copyright year in EULA.
    check: Make sure EULA has proper copyright year.
  - step: Make an attempt to print EULA from installers.
    check: Make sure it is possible.
  - step: Find list of patents and trademarks in EULA.
    check: "Make sure trademarks, copyrights and patents are the same as in http://www.odin.com/legal/"
  - step: Login to Virtuozzo server via ssh
    check: "Make sure search in manual pages works: apropos prlctl."
  - step: Install all available Virtuozzo RPM packages.
    check: Make sure manual pages formatted for 24 columns.
  - step: Find new available options in console utilities.
    check: Make sure all new options are described in manual pages.

- step: Find all Internet links in documentation.
    check: Make sure all these links are alive. In localized edition of product links should be pointed to localized part of the company site.
